    • Method Detail

      • delta

        public int delta()
        Returns the delta of the evaluations for player a and b (evalA - evalB). Evaluating before and after a simulation, the 2 resulting deltas can be used to determine a positive or negative outcome.

      • dot

        public int dot(Simulator.IntEvaluation other)

      • cross

        public int cross(Simulator.IntEvaluation other)

      • subtract

        public Simulator.IntEvaluation subtract(Simulator.IntEvaluation other)
        Subtracts another evaluation and returns the result. Evaluating before and after a simulation, this can be used to calculate before - after. This in turn represents the loss each player had in the meantime.
